description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for an enthusiastic Band 6 Adult Eating Disorder Therapist to join our brand new Specialist Adult Eating Disorder Service (SAEDS). This role will bring opportunities for you to shape and develop our new Adult Eating Disorder Service within North Staffordshire, working together as a part of the multi-disciplinary team. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our new service seeks to provide a high quality service to ensure that clients receive their care by the right person in the right place at the right time, supported by NICE guidance. Enhancing education, prevention, early intervention and strengthened pathways. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for a self-motivated, organised individual who is committed to their role. Part of your role could be to provide specialist interventions and models of treatment to clients within SAEDS, contributing to specialist assessment and treatment planning for clients. If you have a keen interest in supporting adults with eating disorder recovery, then we could be looking for you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This post is full time, working Monday-Friday, 9.00-17.00. The Trust offers Continuing Professional Development (CPD) which is tailored to meet the professional development needs of individual practitioners.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Katie Greensmith&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Deputy Manager Adult Eating Disorder Service&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Katie.greensmith@combined.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;07540 677727&lt;/p&gt;
